text:
Thanks Aki. Yes as a v1, we’re going to do things a bit more custodially. Then we can build out more complete solutions in the next weeks. This will help us move off the DA Utility app asap, and then build up from there.

Ahead of time, we (the eng team) will go through and set up a “Party” on our Canton Validator node for each of our CBTC holders. This will come with a partyId.

When the customer is ready to migrate over:
1. Find the customer’s partyId from a provided spreadsheet (to be provided).
2. Our Bitsafe BD team member will make note of the amount of CC left in their reserve. Then cancel their credential (instructions to follow). They will get back the remaining CC. They can verify this in their wallet.
3. Send to the customer their new partyId value. They can send CC to that address from their wallet. The amount should match the amount of CC that was left in their reserve when we cancelled the credential.
Once they’ve sent it, we’re back in business!

More details to follow, thanks
